arrators find themselves. The book focuses on four key Ontario authors – Stephen Leacock, Robertson Davies, Alice Munro, and Jane Urquhart – as well as many secondary authors, and links the readings to much broader trends in actual Ontario towns and in popular culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Canadian.2bisacsh  aAlice Munro .  aCanadian.  aJane Urquhart.  aOntario.  aRobertson Davies.  aStephen Leacock.  afiction.  aheritage.  aliterature set in Ontario.  aliterature.  amemory.  anovels.  aprovincial.  aregionalism.  arural.  aset in Ontario.  asmall-town.  aurban.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065206240uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148751974240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487519742423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487519742.jpg  a978-3-11-065206-2  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles